# StarShop Frontend — Project Conventions

## Tech Stack
- **Next.js 15** (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4
- **Zustand** for global state, **TanStack React Query** for server state
- **React Hook Form** + **Zod** for forms and validation
- **shadcn/ui** (Radix UI) in `components/ui/` for base primitives
- **Axios** via `lib/api/api.gateway.ts` for all external API calls
- **Sonner** for toast notifications

## Imports
Always use the `@/` path alias. Never use relative `../` imports across feature boundaries.

```ts
// Good
import { api } from "@/lib/api/api.gateway";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

// Bad
import { api } from "../../lib/api/api.gateway";
```

## User Types
The app has three user contexts — route access is enforced in `middleware.ts`:
- **Public** — unauthenticated, `/` and public pages
- **Admin** (`userType: 1`) — `/admin/*`
- **FC / Franchise** (`userType: 2`) — `/fc/*`

## File Naming
- Pages and layouts: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx` (Next.js convention)
- Components: PascalCase with a descriptive suffix — `ProductItemComponent.tsx`, `DashboardCardComponent.tsx`
- Hooks: camelCase prefixed with `use` — `useAuthStore.ts`, `useTeam.ts`
- Types: domain-scoped files under `types/` — `types/orders/index.ts`, `types/admin/order.type.ts`
- Zod schemas: `lib/schema/<section>/<name>.schema.ts`

## TypeScript
- Always type API payloads and responses; import types from `types/`
- Use `ApiResponse<T>` from `@/types/api/api-response` as the standard wrapper
- Avoid `any`; if unavoidable, add `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`

## Notifications
Use `sonner` toast for user feedback:
```ts
import { toast } from "sonner";
toast.success("Saved successfully");
toast.error("Something went wrong");
```
